  "benefit_assessment_plain_language": "M4y turns M4x single GPU-first reuse into a bounded 7-query GPU-first proof. The positive run produced 6 GPU-first cache hits with cpu_overlap_ms=0 and worker_process_ms=0, while exact toy-raw Flye artifacts still matched CPU. selected-only-v0 reduced the positive ledger from the M4x 2886-row full ledger pattern to 35 selected rows, so proof IO/noise is much lower. It is still not an end-to-end speedup: CPU toy-raw took 72s and M4y positive took 74s, because most Flye work remains CPU-bound and the proof still pays session setup, validation, and instrumentation overhead.",
